    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - TRANSFER CASES - REMOVE - SHIFT UNIT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="x1303401" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>SHIFT UNIT</title>
        <para>Depending on the model, the shift unit can be mounted on any one of the output shafts. The removal of each
            of the shift units will be the same, regardless of the position.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove air lines if required.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove locknut and washer from output shaft. Remove end yoke or companion flange.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disengage shift unit by pulling the shifter shaft up or out.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove nine (9) bolts and lockwashers from flange of disconnect. Remove disconnect by
                lifting straight away from case
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303401">(Figure 1)</hotlnk>. Remove gasket and discard.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303401" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg13/g1303401.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Remove Disconnect</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove needle roller bearing from output shaft
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303402">(Figure 2)</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303402" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg13/g1303402.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Remove Needle Roller Bearing From Output Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
